HEADWORD: Bostryx
<hw>Bos"tryx</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL.; irreg. fr.
Gr. <?/ a curl.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A form of cymose
inflorescence with all the flowers on one side of the rachis, usually
causing it to curl; -- called also a <altname>uniparous helicoid
cyme</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

